<TITLE> AL to launch 'mass communication' tour </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 10 (bdnews24.com)  The ruling Awami League will launch a month-long 'mass communication' tour across the country from March 18. Party leaders will start the tour from seven divisions in 16 separate groups,. "Apart from mass communication and recruiting members, the leaders will inform people about the government's achievement over the last year and make people aware of the opposition's 'negative' politics," joint general secretary Mahbub ul Hanif told reporters on Wednesday after the presidium meeting at Dhanmondi. "We want people to create pressure on the four-party alliance to refrain from its negative politics," Hanif said. "We also want to hear what people expect from the government." The tour will finish before the monsoon, he said. The composition of the groups will be announced later in the month, the AL leader said. b
